.TH "vmw_crtc_state_and_lock" 9 "vmw_crtc_state_and_lock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_crtc_state_and_lock \- Return new or current crtc state with locked crtc mutex
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_crtc_state *" vmw_crtc_state_and_lock
.BI "(struct drm_atomic_state *state "  ","
.BI "struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
The atomic state pointer containing the new atomic state
.IP "crtc" 12
The crtc
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function returns the new crtc state if it's part of the state update.
Otherwise returns the current crtc state. It also makes sure that the
crtc mutex is locked.
.SH "RETURN"
A valid crtc state pointer or NULL. It may also return a
pointer error, in particular -EDEADLK if locking needs to be rerun.
